description.p:
Friction reduction systems (3) can be of different nature and are generally known devices. Quite simply two tapered roller bearings can be used, but the solution that has shown the best combination in terms of compactness, load supporting capacity and life cycle duration foresees the use of:
on the outer side of the wheel (2), a pair of matched tapered roller bearings arranged face-to-face (34, 35), which acts as a hinge, supporting both axial and radial loads;
on the inner side of the wheels (2), a thin toroidal roller bearing (33), for example the CARB® bearing manufactured by SKF®, which acts as a support, supporting only radial loads.
